Deon Goldschmidt, Esq 

FAQ:
What is a personal injury attorney?

" What is a personal injury attorney? Well, personal injury attorneys are employed by consumers who have been involved in some misfortune or accident in which they've suffered bodily injury. Those accidents can be from all different types of situations:

  • Product defects where a product explodes or breaks causing injury to a party
  • Car accidents where somebody is injured as the result of negligent driving
  • Motorcycle accidents
  • A slip and fall or trip and fall case at the grocery store
  • Medical malpractice

Generally, personal injury firms take cases on a no-win no fee basis."

OTHER FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS

Is it worth getting an injury attorney?

Certainly, the answer is yes, an experienced injury attorney will know the value of your case and will ensure that the insurance company pays you just compensation for your injuries.

When should you contact a personal injury lawyer?

First things first take care of your urgent medical needs, thereafter call an injury attorney at your first convenience before you start any communications with the guilty parties insurance company, they are not there to help you, they are there to pay you as little as possible.

Do I need a lawyer for pain and suffering?

Yes, the compensation you receive for your injuries will include compensation for pain and suffering. An experienced attorney knows how to translate the extent of your pain and suffering into compensation, without an experienced injury attorney you will be at the mercy of the insurance adjuster.

How much should I sue for pain and suffering?

The answer to this question will depend on the facts of your case, in general, the more treatment you have and the longer and more complex the treatment the more you can claim for pain and suffering. Only an experienced injury attorney can answer this question based on your individual set of circumstances.

What is a good settlement offer?

This will depend on the nature and extent of your injuries and the time and nature of the treatment received as well as the extent of wages lost as a result of injury and what future medical treatment is required going forward. Each case is unique and must be assessed by an experienced injury attorney.

Choosing the right lawyer to represent you is crucial to the outcome of your case. Our attorneys have a proven track record, have presented victims of all types of injuries. Experience, Results Driven, Trusted and Respected are all key factors when you are hiring a law firm to represent you or your loved ones who are victims and suffered injuries from an accident. Call our San Diego office today. Get your FREE consultation.

If you reside in San Diego and have suffered an injury, heres some useful information:

Do I Have a Personal Injury Claim?

If youve been hurt through no fault of your own, you may have a case. Personal injury lawsuits attempt to recover financial damages from the negligent party to compensate the victim for their injuries. Although money can never completely make up for the pain and suffering that a severe injuries causes to the victim and their family, adequate compensation can relieve the financial distress that usually results from an unexpected tragedy. In other words, let the best San Diego Personal Injury Attorney help you stop worrying about paying the bills so that you can focus your energy on whats really important, your recovery.

Personal injuries can be a result of the actions, the inaction or the negligence of one or more individuals or organizations. The most common causes include car accidents, medical malpractice, wrongful death and workplace accidents, but anytime youre injured due to no fault of your own, it can fall under the legal definition of personal injury. When your claim is presented in a court of law, you must prove that the other party was both liable and negligent to recover. This means that they were legally required to exercise a certain level of care, they failed to do so and that you were injured or damaged in some way.

How Can a San Diego Personal Injury Lawyer Help Me?

You can rely on the skills and knowledge of an experienced lawyer to know the relevant laws and case studies inside and out. Our attorneys will look at your claim from a completely different viewpoint to identify all the possible angles to maximize your compensation package while ensuring that no detail, no matter how small, is overlooked.

Of course, the insurance company may tell you something different. They are trained to give you the impression that they are acting in good faith and protecting your interests while trying to minimize their financial exposure. Heres a little secret: Even your insurance company doesnt work to protect your interests when it comes to a payout. In San Diego and around the world their ultimate responsibility is to pay you as little as possible and avoid an expensive lawsuit.

If an insurance company or a large business is involved in your personal injury claim, here are a few reasons that consulting with a specialized lawyer is critical:
  • Youre Outmatched Organizations of this size have an entire team of expert attorney and other professionals who share a common goal: to pay as little as possible to injury victims. Never attempt to take them on without your own attorney, you are not alone.
  • Youre Too Close to the Issue Personal injury is, well, very personal, and you wouldnt be human if you didnt feel emotional about the entire situation. Although the staff at an insurance company or other business wont pay more than they have to, the final number doesnt mean they wont be able to pay their bills or send their children to college. In addition to having years of experience in these matters, this will always give them the upper hand at the bargaining table when you try to negotiate with them directly.
  • You Cant Afford to Wait The insurance company has all the time in the world, but you dont. Knowing that your bills are piling up, they may give you a low-ball offer on the chance that youll take it out of desperation. An experienced attorney who has handled hundreds of cases just like yours will be able to advise you on the fairness of any offer as well as what you can gain by filing a lawsuit.
  • You Dont Know Their Tactics Big business knows that you arent a legal expert, and they take full advantage of it. Dont expect them tell you about your legal rights or the applicable statute of limitations. They certainly wont preserve any evidence that isnt legally required.

Most of all, an experienced legal professional will provide you with peace of mind and the time to heal. Once you have expert knowledge and years of experience on your side, youll feel like youve started to take control of the situation, and your life, once again. If youve been losing sleep worrying about negotiating with the insurance company and meeting your financial obligations, a single consultation with our accident attorneys will be better than any sleeping pill! Once your energy is refocused on your recovery and your familys needs, youll literally feel like a heavy weight has been lifted from your shoulders!

Protect Yourself and Your Loved Ones in the Event of an Injury. Consult with an experienced San Diego personal injury attorney.

If you or someone you care about is injured due to someone elses negligence, take these steps to protect your interests:

  • Do not wait to seek medical care in San Diego or outside San Diego. Delays can raise several questions including whether you were really hurt, the date of the injury or the actual source of the damage. Keep records of every doctor you see and how you feel on a daily basis.
  • Record the names of witnesses and other pertinent facts. If youre able, create a file with all relevant information. Write down your own account of the accident as soon as you can just in case your memory of the event fades with time. Keep track of every medical expense and your lost time from work.
  • Consult with legal counsel based in San Diego as soon as possible. Only an experienced attorney can advise you of your rights and your responsibilities in a personal injury case. Most lawyers offer free consultations with no obligation. Never sign any legal documents or speak to anyone without your own representation.

San Diego Personal Injury Attorneys are available 24/7 and we'll come to you no matter what city you are in!
